Why must I buy the same things she wore?

65
00:07:15,723 --> 00:07:17,004
What's so different about me and Kim?

66
00:07:17,724 --> 00:07:19,945
Is it because she can wear a dress of ridiculous value?

67
00:07:20,386 --> 00:07:22,126
Or because she buys the most expensive things?

68
00:07:22,847 --> 00:07:27,249
Last time I checked, me and Kim both need air to breathe, food to survive, and a home for safety.

69
00:07:27,709 --> 00:07:31,511
But because I do not own the same overpriced dress Kim wore, I am ignored.

70
00:07:32,191 --> 00:07:38,434
The scenario may seem normal, but when you switch the roles to a middle class man and a homeless man, the situation is turned immediately.

71
00:07:39,344 --> 00:07:45,730
Suddenly the lower class person is ignored, but being put down in negative terms, which is lazy, drug addict, slob, trash, and worse.

72
00:07:46,331 --> 00:07:55,781
